parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a spongy brake pedal, reduced braking performance, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
symptoms: vehicle pulls to one side while braking
excessive wear on rotors and pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake hardware, such as brake shoes, drums, or calipers, can cause reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
symptoms: excessive wear on rotors and pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake dragging can cause reduced fuel efficiency, increased wear on brake components, and overheating of brakes, which can lead to brake failure.
The unintended deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

symptoms: Squeaking or grinding noise while driving
and sudden drops in vehicle height.
